---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="AI, CRM, websites, and local SEO services in Thunder Bay | ThunderBayAI" description="Explore ThunderBayAI service pathways for AI automation, CRM systems, website systems, local SEO, and lead generation in Thunder Bay and Northwestern Ontario." ogImage="/images/generated/003-luxury-ai-product-website-artwork-for-a-.png">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container split-panel">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Services hub</p>
        <h1>Service pathways for businesses that want cleaner systems, better visibility, and more qualified local demand.</h1>
        <p class="lead">ThunderBayAI helps owners understand where AI, CRM, websites, and local SEO fit. When it is time to implement, the path routes into Frayze. The point is not more tools. The point is a better growth system.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button" href="/ai-opportunity-audit">Start with an AI Audit</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="https://frayze.ca/book-consultation/">Book Strategy Call</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="showcase-frame">
          <img src="/images/generated/003-luxury-ai-product-website-artwork-for-a-.png" alt="Premium service-page visual showing elegant AI dashboards and analytics interfaces in a luxury environment." />
          <div class="showcase-badge">
            <p class="eyebrow">Premium service architecture</p>
            <p class="muted" style="margin:0;">Authority on the front end. Implementation path on the back end. Every page should make the next move obvious.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container grid grid-2">
      <a class="card card-link" href="/thunder-bay-ai-automation">
        <p class="eyebrow">AI automation</p>
        <h3>Thunder Bay AI Automation</h3>
        <p class="muted">Identify the manual bottlenecks, missed leads, and slow follow-up steps that should be automated first.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card card-link" href="/thunder-bay-crm-systems">
        <p class="eyebrow">CRM systems</p>
        <h3>Thunder Bay CRM Systems</h3>
        <p class="muted">Build a cleaner pipeline, stronger follow-up, and better visibility from inquiry to booked job.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card card-link" href="/thunder-bay-local-seo">
        <p class="eyebrow">Local SEO</p>
        <h3>Thunder Bay Local SEO</h3>
        <p class="muted">Improve how local businesses show up when buyers are actively looking for help.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card card-link" href="/thunder-bay-website-systems">
        <p class="eyebrow">Website systems</p>
        <h3>Thunder Bay Website Systems</h3>
        <p class="muted">Move beyond brochure sites into websites that support lead capture, qualification, and conversion.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card card-link" href="/thunder-bay-lead-generation-systems">
        <p class="eyebrow">Lead generation</p>
        <h3>Thunder Bay Lead Generation Systems</h3>
        <p class="muted">Combine visibility, conversion infrastructure, follow-up, and reporting into one growth engine.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card card-link" href="/ai-opportunity-audit">
        <p class="eyebrow">Lead magnet</p>
        <h3>AI Opportunity Audit</h3>
        <p class="muted">Start with a practical audit to see what should be automated, fixed, or tightened before spending blindly.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card card-link" href="/automation-opportunity-scorecard">
        <p class="eyebrow">Tool</p>
        <h3>Automation Opportunity Scorecard</h3>
        <p class="muted">A lightweight scorecard to see whether your business should prioritize automation, CRM cleanup, or conversion fixes next.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container grid grid-2">
      <a class="card card-link" href="/missed-lead-calculator">
        <p class="eyebrow">Tool</p>
        <h3>Missed Lead Calculator</h3>
        <p class="muted">A simple lead magnet that estimates how much missed calls and weak follow-up may be costing each month.</p>
      </a>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Routing model</p>
        <p class="muted">ThunderBayAI captures attention and educates. Frayze handles implementation. Every strong page should reinforce that handoff cleanly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
